My whole point in this entire thing is to say that they are good people and boycotting them is silly. You getting all up-in-arms about it isn't my problem. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Unless you can PROVE I am lying, which you can't, making a statement like that does nothing but inspire an answer like this.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Ok. I'll prove it to you next time I log on.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Your claim that it is folks in the main US complaining is arrogant as well. How do you know all the posters here in this thread, and the ones on other boards discussing this, are US, Canadian, Mexican, European, British, Chinese, Australian, or any other nationality? The answer, you don't.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Now, you're right here about a couple things. I don't know. And I am arrogant. However, I *do* know that a number of the guilds boycotting them are based in the US time zones. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  So, my statement not to base your statements on things you have not experienced is actually right on the money, you are just POed that anyone dared refute you.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
No dear, that's where you're sadly mistaken. I'm not POed at anyone, actually. And I'm hardly arrogant enough to get POed over someone disagreeing.<br>
